Review: You know when you’re watching something where a manic pixie dream girl falls in love with the bad boy and she’s like “I can fix him” and you’re like Baby, no you can’t? That’s what it’s like watching Japanese guys with ptsd try to kill Godzilla. Movie after movie, they delude themselves into thinking that their hare-brained idea is gonna be the one that works. Pam couldn’t fix Tommy and you can’t kill Godzilla. Sorry.
I could feel my hand clenching into a fist when she stepped on the scale fully pregnant and was only 130 lbs. I like when she does karate tho
Props to Bruce Willis for being secure enough in his manhood to be a lead in this because it’s probably the gayest movie I’ve ever seen (in a good way)
I lol-ed when she did the dance that made her husband want to fuck her. Lol-ed a few times actually and I love the poster
*shouting* AHHHH TURN IT OFF (Actually I kind of liked some parts)
Shyamalan is a Philly boy I wonder if this is based on that wildlife refuge in tinicum by the airport because I would sooner believe there’s a 19th century town in there than a single animal
Seriously good movie. I love long movies because u get to spend hours of your day in a dark room not talking without feeling like maybe you should be doing something else
I don’t know how it gets better than this

I got home from work and my bf and his friend were watching this and they told me the title but I immediately forgot it and then about 30 mins later I started to ask (in reference to the main character) “is he supposed to be some sort of night watchman?” and remembered
